results.lead_paragraph: Apollo 17 ends for the foreseeable future the era of intensive American preoccupation with lunar exploration. This country has no firm plans for sending either manned or unmanned rockets to the moon. NASA's lunar planning after Apollo 17 focuses primarily on further study of the rocks Apollo crews have brought back, as well as following the reports radioed back by instruments placed on the moon by astronauts.

results.abstract: damage to Hanoi's civil airport at Gia Lam by US bombing in last few days prevents USSR Aeroflot flight to Hanoi; flight was to have brought USSR Cosmonaut G Titov to Hanoi and to have left with 4 Amers; Amers are T Taylor, J Baez, Rev M Allen and B Romo; USSR plane waits at Rangoon, Burma, for N Vietnamese clearance before proceeding to Vientiane, Laos, and Hanoi; speculation is that if US call off raids on Hanoi over Christmas weekend, flight would proceed
results.snippet: VIENTIANE, Laos, Dec. 23 -A flight that was to have brought Soviet Cosmonaut German Titov to Hanoi and to have departed with four Americans who have been there for the past week has been postponed.
